CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 2, 1956, pg. A20 reads: "D.I.'s Present Scholarship - Mrs. Mamie Lee, right, accepts a scholarship award from the D.I.'s Club chairman, Juanita Drake, while other members look on. First row, left to right, the awardee, Mary Dee, Mrs. Drake and Gay DeHall.  Second row: Gladys Cralle, Ruby Young and Elaine Jones. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of seven women, including first row: Mamie Lee, accepting scholarship award from D.I. Club chairman Juanita Drake, Mary Dee, and Gay DeHall; second row: Gladys Cralle, Ruby Young Buchanan and Elaine Jones, posed in interior with bay window and wood paneled staircase
